      "writtenOn": "2020-12-14T17:37:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is throwing me a little, but maybe I just don\u0027t know the SkSL lingo.  I would have thought we\u0027d have Variables holding Values, not Locations holding Variables.  Is Location an indirection between Variables/Expressions and Values?\n\nThink we can get a quick primer up here at the top explaining the relationships between Variable, Expression, Location, Value?  (The declaration of Value did at least make it pretty clear the relationship between Value and skvm::Val.)\n\nIs a Variable itself not an expression?  Or I guess, is it something like\n\n    Location getLocation(const Variable\u0026 v) { return this-\u003egetLocation(RValue(v)); }\n\n?",
      "revId": "00457109a7057031474ceb80244b7d4b0b240bfa",
